==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|chekmat}}, from {{der|en|fro|eschec mat}}, from {{der|en|ar|شَاه مَاتَ}}, from {{der|en|fa|شاه مات|tr=šâh mât|t=the king [is] amazed}}. Perhaps conflated with {{der|en|ar| مَاتَ|t=to die}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈt͡ʃɛkmeɪt/}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-checkmate.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|eɪt}}

===Interjection===
{{en-interj}}

# {{lb|en|chess}} Word called out by the [[victor]] when making a move that wins the game.
# {{lb|en|by extension}} Said when one has placed a person in a losing situation with no escape.

